    htmlContent:
      '<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;"><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Uneven skin texture, fine lines, acne scars, pigmentation, and sun damage are common skin concerns that develop over time. When topical treatments and routine skincare are not enough, </span><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;">laser skin resurfacing</span><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"> offers an advanced and effective solution. At </span><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;">Luxor Hospital</span><span style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">, treatments are performed using modern technology and medical expertise to improve skin quality safely and gradually.</span></p><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">What Is Laser Skin Resurfacing?</h2><p style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Laser skin resurfacing is a dermatological procedure that uses focused laser energy to remove damaged skin layers and stimulate new skin cell growth. It also boosts collagen production, helping improve skin firmness, texture, and tone.</p><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Skin Concerns Treated with Laser Resurfacing</h2><ul style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><li>Acne scars and surgical scars</li><li>Fine lines and wrinkles</li><li>Sun-damaged skin</li><li>Uneven skin tone and pigmentation</li><li>Enlarged pores</li><li>Rough or dull skin texture</li></ul><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Types of Laser Skin Resurfacing</h2><p style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><b>Ablative Lasers:</b> Remove the outer layer of damaged skin. Ideal for deeper scars and wrinkles but require longer recovery.</p><p style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><b>Non-Ablative Lasers:</b> Heat deeper skin layers without removing the surface. Suitable for mild to moderate concerns with minimal downtime.</p><p style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><b>Fractional Lasers:</b> Treat only a fraction of the skin at a time, allowing faster healing with effective results. Commonly used for Indian skin types.</p><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Benefits of Laser Skin Resurfacing</h2><ul style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><li>Smoother skin texture</li><li>Reduction in scars and wrinkles</li><li>Improved skin tone and clarity</li><li>Enhanced collagen production</li><li>Long-lasting skin rejuvenation</li></ul><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Risks and Side Effects</h2><p style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">When performed by trained specialists, laser skin resurfacing is safe. Temporary side effects may include redness, swelling, mild discomfort, temporary pigmentation changes, and skin sensitivity.</p><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Downtime and Recovery</h2><ul style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><li><b>Non-ablative lasers:</b> Return to routine within 1–2 days</li><li><b>Fractional lasers:</b> Mild redness for a few days</li><li><b>Ablative lasers:</b> Recovery may take 1–2 weeks</li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Sun protection and gentle skincare are essential during recovery.</p><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Who Is an Ideal Candidate?</h2><ul style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><li>Individuals with realistic expectations</li><li>Free from active skin infections</li><li>Seeking non-surgical skin rejuvenation</li><li>Willing to follow post-treatment care</li></ul><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Why Choose Luxor Hospital?</h2><ul style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><li>Experienced dermatologists</li><li>Advanced laser technology</li><li>Safe protocols for Indian skin</li><li>Personalized treatment plans</li><li>Complete pre- and post-procedure care</li></ul><h2 style="font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:#ac8f5a;margin-top:18pt;">Final Thoughts</h2><p style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Laser skin resurfacing is an effective solution for improving skin texture, tone, and overall appearance. With proper evaluation, expert execution, and aftercare, patients can achieve noticeable and lasting skin rejuvenation.</p>',
